The paper discusses an AI-based explanation system and its effectiveness in enabling end users to understand, assess, and trust intelligent agents. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The domain of real-time strategy games also suggests a potential focus on game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the construction of explanations, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL).
